Print an Indicator Time Series Object

Source: R/print_methods.R
print.indicator_ts.Rd

Provides a summary representation of an indicator_ts object, designed for user-friendly display in the console.

Usage

# S3 method for class 'indicator_ts'
print(x, n = 10, ...)

Arguments

x

An indicator_ts object.

n

Integer specifying the number of rows of data to display.

...

Additional arguments.

Examples

print(example_indicator_ts1)
#> Biodiversity indicator time series
#> 
#> Name of indicator: Observed Species Richness 
#> 
#> Date Range: 1970 - 2023 
#> 
#> Region(s) represented: Denmark
